<title type="html"><![CDATA[Simple Saturn Game Hack]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5416&amp;p=48973#p48973"><![CDATA[
I recently bought Pandemonium for my iPhone and as I played it, I realized it has a very Sonic the Hedgehog speed and feel to it.  Since there is no real Sonic game for the Saturn (3D blast sucks, Sonic Jam was a compilation and Sonic R is just a joke) and Pandemonium was originally a Saturn/PSX game, I got to thinkin: How hard would it be to hack in the 3D model for Sonic from Sonic R to replace the female character in Pandemonium?  She even does a forward flip when you double jump, making it an almost perfect transition for a Sonic model.  I don't know what kind of knowledge is out there and how difficult it is to hack Saturn games, but I figured if anyone knew, they would probably hang out around here.  I just think it would be hella cool to put Sonic in Pandemonium given the gameplay and level design is dead on to what a good Sonic game should be.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3414">17daysolderthannes</a> — Thu Jul 16, 2009 10:01 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
